The Senate has admitted the Inspector General of Police, Mr Mohammed Adamu into the chamber to brief lawmakers on the nation’s security challenges. The session is holding behind-closed-doors. IGP, NSCDC Boss summoned by Reps over ‘accidental discharge’ Recall that last week, the Senate summoned Mr. Adamu following fears that the wave of crimes across the nation is on the rise again. Mr. Adamu is expected to address the lawmakers on the concept and practical implementation modalities of community policing policy.